  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3554570641" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3554570641" />
    <a title="Woman Reading" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/101060033-woman-reading"><img alt="Woman Reading" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1565479291p2/101060033.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3554570641?book_show_action=true">Sep 19, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Woman Reading" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Woman Reading" href="/user/show/101060033-woman-reading">Woman Reading</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/101060033-woman-reading?shelf=4-stars-very-good">4-stars-very-good</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/101060033-woman-reading?shelf=read-women-2020-challenge">read-women-2020-challenge</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/101060033-woman-reading?shelf=fantasy-urban-fantasy">fantasy-urban-fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3554570641" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6405182149278662970"><b>4 ☆ </b><br/><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i> Even after all this time, I keep forgetting that heroes can be found in unlikely places and persons - like mechanics who can turn into coyotes.</i>
  </b>
</blockquote> <br/><i> Blood Bound</i> #2 can be read as a standalone as the Mercy Thompson stories feel episodic in nature. Mercy&apos;s life changes as the series progresses but she doesn&apos;t have a major life quest, unlike other main protagonists in urban fantasy series. <blockquote>
  <b>
    <i> I struggled to live in a world with no place for me... I&apos;d been raised by the pack but I</i></b></blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText6405182149278662970" style="display:none"><b>4 ☆ </b><br /><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i> Even after all this time, I keep forgetting that heroes can be found in unlikely places and persons - like mechanics who can turn into coyotes.</i>
  </b>
</blockquote> <br /><i> Blood Bound</i> #2 can be read as a standalone as the Mercy Thompson stories feel episodic in nature. Mercy's life changes as the series progresses but she doesn't have a major life quest, unlike other main protagonists in urban fantasy series. <blockquote>
  <b>
    <i> I struggled to live in a world with no place for me... I'd been raised by the pack but I wasn't one of them. My mother loved me, but I didn't belong in her mundane human world either... I had to make my own path in life rather than finding someone else's to join.</i>
  </b>
</blockquote> <br />Mercy is an underdog within the supernatural pantheon as she shifts into a 35 pound coyote. So she's learned to straddle a fine line to keep her independence and to remain safe among the human-eating Fae, the blood-drinking vampires, and the much larger and stronger werewolves with their chauvinistic attitudes. Werewolves aren't soft and fluffy, but as Mercy can also become one of the furry creatures, sympathy veers toward them. This just makes Briggs' focus on vampires in <i> Blood Bound </i> all the more terrifying as the ante is upped with a supercharged vampire as the villain. Horror isn't a common genre for me, so a couple of scenes caused my pulse to accelerate in a nervous fashion. <br /><br />Mercy is a proactive woman with a strong moral code. She's not one to seek trouble but it easily manages to find her. <i>Blood Bound</i> begins with Mercy paying back a favor to Stefan, her sole vampire friend, who wants her to witness a meeting with a vampire stranger. Mercy survives the meeting but emerges with extensive bruising and a commonsensical terror of the vampire who reeks of blood and sulfur. As the demon-ridden vampire continues his serial murder spree, the magnitude of the danger to all ensnares the werewolves' involvement. The ensuing events become so dire that not even a brave underdog can wait patiently at the sidelines. <blockquote>
  <b>
    <i> "Then again, maybe you couldn't have killed me," he said, crawling out of the stairway. He moved very slowly, like a lizard who had gotten too cold.<br /><br />I heard a whimper from behind one of the closed doors next to the bathroom, and sympathized. I wanted to whimper, too.<br /><br />"I'm not hunting you," I told him firmly, though I stepped backward until I stood in a circle of light at the end of the hallway.<br /><br />He stopped halfway out of the stairway, his eyes were filmed over like a dead man's.<br /><br />"Good," he said. "If you kill <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[Andre, <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> I won't tell and no one will ask."<br /><br />And he was gone, withdrawing from the hallway and down the stairs so fast that I barely caught the motion, though I was staring right at him.<br /><br />I walked out of his home because if I'd moved any faster, I'd have run screaming.</i>
  </b>
</blockquote> <br />The pacing of <i>Blood Bound</i> felt occasionally uneven as Briggs used brief respites to flesh out more details about the werewolves or other people in Mercy's circle. Overall though, it was a good and scary installment in the series.<br /><br /><br />#0.3 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3617613377" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>Homecoming</i> 3 ☆ </a><br />#1 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3552085188" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>Moon Called</i> 3.5 ☆ </a><br />#3 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3558226248" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>Iron Kissed</i> 4 ☆</a><br />#4 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3559749109" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>Bones Crossed</i> 3.5 ☆</a><br />#5 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3561364186" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>Silver Borne </i> 3.5 ☆ </a> <br />#6 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3563109879" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>River Marked</i> 4 ☆</a> <br />#7 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3567582608" rel="nofollow noopener"><i>Frost Burned</i> 3.5 ☆</a><br />#7.5 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3628758921" rel="nofollow noopener"><i>Hopcross Jilly</i> 3.5 ☆</a><br />#8 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3567593934" rel="nofollow noopener"><i> Night Broken </i> 4 ☆</a><br />#9 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3569162915" rel="nofollow noopener"><i>Fire Touched</i> 3.5 ☆</a><br />#10 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3570979313" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>Silence Fallen </i>almost 4☆</a><br />#11 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3570986261" rel="nofollow noopener"> <i>Storm Cursed</i> 4 ☆</a> <br />#12 <a href="https://www.Goodreads.com/review/show/3586947598" rel="nofollow noopener"><i> Smoke Bitten</i> 3 ☆</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="6405182149278662970" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
